01/07/2007
STRUGA, Macedonia -- Menduh Thaci was elected the new leader of the Democratic Party of Albanians (DPA), during a party congress in Struga on Saturday (June 30th). Thaci, formerly DPA deputy chair, succeeds longtime leader Arben Xhaferri. He was the sole candidate for the post. Following his election, Thaci pledged to consolidate the party and work to make a multiethnic Macedonia the "Brussels of Southeast Europe". (Makfax, A1 TV, Telma TV - 30/06/07)
